        <h2>General Notes</h2>
        <p>When two medicines are administered to a patient they may either act independently of each other, or interact with each other.  Interaction may increase or decrease the effect of the medicines concerned, and may cause unexpected toxicity. As newer and more potent medicines are available to us, the number of serious medicine interactions occurring is likely to increase.</p>
        <p>Remember that interactions may involve non-prescription medicines and social drugs (such as alcohol, mbanje), plants and traditional remedies.</p>
